			<p><b>Haguro Operational Timeline</b></p><table border='0' cellspacing='0'><tr bgcolor='eeeeee'><td valign='top' align='right' nowrap><a href='/event/today/04/25/1929' alt='See all events on 25 Apr 1929' title='See all events on 25 Apr 1929' class='noStyle'>25 Apr 1929</a>&nbsp;</td><td>Haguro was commissioned into service.</td></tr><tr bgcolor=''><td valign='top' align='right' nowrap><a href='/event/today/05/15/1945' alt='See all events on 15 May 1945' title='See all events on 15 May 1945' class='noStyle'>15 May 1945</a>&nbsp;</td><td>British destroyer forces sank the Japanese cruiser Haguro in the Malacca Strait off the Malay Peninsula.</td></tr><tr bgcolor='eeeeee'><td valign='top' align='right' nowrap><a href='/event/today/05/16/1945' alt='See all events on 16 May 1945' title='See all events on 16 May 1945' class='noStyle'>16 May 1945</a>&nbsp;</td><td>Aircraft from escort carrier HMS Emperor attacked Japanese cruiser Haguro at the entrance of the Malacca Strait.</td></tr></table><br /><p><b>Photographs</b></p><table cellpadding='2' cellspacing='0' border='0'><tr><td><a href='/photo.php?source=all&color=all&list=search&foreigntype=S&foreigntype_id=87'><img src="/images/imagemagick/tmb_ship_haguro14.jpg" border='0' alt='Haguro under construction in Drydock No. 3 of the Mitsubishi shipyard in Nagasaki, Japan, 20 Oct 1928'></a></td><td><a href='/photo.php?source=all&color=all&list=search&foreigntype=S&foreigntype_id=87'><img src="/images/imagemagick/tmb_ship_haguro2.jpg" border='0' alt='Haguro in the final stages of fitting out, off Mutusbishi's Nagasaki shipyard, Japan, 6 Apr 1929'></a></td><td><a href='/photo.php?source=all&color=all&list=search&foreigntype=S&foreigntype_id=87'><img src="/images/imagemagick/tmb_ship_haguro4.jpg" border='0' alt='Haguro, probably between Dec 1931 and Nov 1932 when she was the third-ranking ship of Japanese Navy's Cruiser Squadron 4, Fourth Fleet; Japanese inscription in the lower right reads 'Large cruiser Hag'></a></td><td><a h